## Assignment 3: WordPress Child Theme

### Overview

For this assignment, I created a child theme based on my Metro Report theme from Assignment 2. The goal was to customize the design without changing the original parent theme files.

---

### Setup

I created a child theme folder with:

- style.css (theme header and custom styles)
- functions.php (loads parent and child styles)
- single.php (custom layout for posts)
- page.php (custom layout for pages)

---

### Customizations

I improved the layout by:

- adding a card-style design to homepage posts
- centering content and improving spacing
- increasing title size for better readability
- styling pages with a boxed layout

---

### Templates

- single.php shows post title, author, date, and content  
- page.php shows title and content only  

---

### Reflection

This assignment helped me understand how child themes work and how to safely customize a WordPress site. I also learned how template files control different parts of the site layout.
